   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   },
   "source": [
    "## using ``in authors`` search field\n",
    "\n",
    "Usecase\n",
    "* Exact name search. We have a special search index for name+surname combinations. This will give you better results than using 'where'.\n",
    "\n",
    "Features\n",
    "* requires exact name + surname\n",
    "* can have boolean operators inside the search string (AND, OR, MUST, SHOULD)\n",
    "* Limitations: can't be used in combination with other full text search operators.\n",
    "* Asterisks cannot be used as it is slow"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

       "_stats": {
        "total_count": 0
       },
       "publications": []
      },

    "# fails as the inner quotes are missing\n",

    "# works with AND and OR, plus a field filter\n",
    "q = \"\"\"( \\\\\"Michele Pasin\\\\\" AND \\\\\"V Lopez\\\\\" ) OR ( \\\\\"Michele Pasin\\\\\" AND \\\\\"J Bradley\\\\\" )\"\"\"\n",
    "dsl.query(f\"\"\"search publications in authors for \"{q}\" where year in [2010:2019] return publications\"\"\")"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## using ``where authors`` field \n",
    "\n",
    "Usecase\n",
    "* Partial name search. Any combination of name or surname words is allowed. Of course this returns more results.\n",
    "\n",
    "Features\n",
    "* it can be used in combination with other full text search operators (eg search in title_abstract)\n",
    "* does not allow boolean operators in search string\n",
    "* allows for partial matched using the ~ operator (asterisk and other special chars are stripped out)"
   ]
